name: about-pos
summary: Provide more meta info while you  loop back/forth on your arrays.
description:
Whenever I loop through an array, there are times I wish I could
    know what comes before or after the item I am currently one.
    Including prev/next index calculations.  This gem helps you with
    that. However, it would be better for you to create your own
    since you will probably not like my way of doing it.

If you were to be an onmyoji (an yin-yang exorcist), this gem would help your work.

name: auto-click
summary: Smulating mouse click, cursor movement and keystrokes
description:
Provide several Ruby methods for simulating mouse click, cursor movement and keystrokes in Windows. 
                     This gem use DL library and SendInput method so there is no dependency on FFI, AutoIt or Win32-api. 
                     Methods include mouse_move(x,y), left_click, right_click, type(string), mouse_scroll(steps), key_up, key_down...etc.
                     See https://github.com/erinata/auto_click for more details about instalation and usage.
                     (More control over mouse movement such as speed or locus will be implemented in future releases)

name: murmuring-spider
summary: MurmuringSpider is a concise Twitter crawler with DataMapper.
description:
MurmuringSpider is a concise Twitter crawler.

When we write a data-mining / text-mining application based on twitter timeline, we have to collect and store tweets first.

I am irritated with writing such crawler repeatedly, so I wrote this.

What you have to do is only to add query and to run them periodically.

Thanks to consistent Twitter API and twitter gem (http://twitter.rubyforge.org/), it is quite easy to track various types of timelines (such as user_timeline, home_timeline, search...)
